review_blob: Pretty light and thin. Smells of grass and tastes the same with a clean light bitterness. Lawn mower beer.

Two words, "hop syrup"! I get heavy grapefruit on the nose with resiny pine. Bitter grapefruit and a touch of orange up front with hop bitterness that creeps up intensely on the back end and then cleanly dissipates rather quickly making you want to come back for more. Malt adds nice sweetness and amazing syrupy mouthfeel. Definitely one of my new favorite IPAs.
So good. Sweet and slightly tart cherry on the front end with subtle chipotle heat on the back end that lingers ever slightly (welcoming). Great for a cold winter night!
Great tropical fruit flavors with grapefruit and orange at the forefront. Also get some earthy/grassy flavors. Fantastic IPA. Actually reminds me a little bit of Columbus IPA.
beer_name: The Brew Kettle White Rajah IPA
